<topic id='class_location.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Class: LOCATION - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A physical 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>.        </p>
    <p>This could be:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>
where 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 are seen                    </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>
where 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICES</xref>
 exist                    </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>
from which requests for 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITIES</xref>
 are sent or                    </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>
any other place of interest to an 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 which is not recorded as an 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 or an 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation_site">ORGANISATION SITE</xref>.                    </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
For 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITIES</xref>
 provided by staff groups, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATIONS</xref>
 are places where a face-to-face contact or a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_group_session">Group Session</xref>
 occurs.        </p>
    <p>
For diagnostic 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITIES</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATIONS</xref>
 either define the whereabouts of the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITY</xref>
 or the places from which requests are sent.        </p>
    <p>
Each 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>
 must be classified by one and only one type of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>
 and the same classification must be used by all users.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
